cs.LG, cs.IR, cs.SI, cs.AI, cs.DS

This paper proposes a model for predictive tasks on dynamic relational data, which involves the use of neural networks and tensor factorization. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.LG (Machine Learning), which covers topics related to neural networks and deep learning. 

The paper also deals with recommender systems and information retrieval, which suggests that it could also belong to cs.IR (Information Retrieval) as a secondary sub-category. 

Additionally, the paper addresses the issue of evolving user preferences over time, which could fall under cs.SI (Social and Information Networks) as it deals with dynamic relational data. 

The use of non-linearities between different latent factors also suggests that the paper could belong to cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence), which covers topics related to machine learning and decision making. 

Finally, the paper involves extensive experiments and evaluation, which could also place it under cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) as it deals with the analysis and manipulation of data.
